        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 md:col-span-2">
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/60">Overview</div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-white/75">
            Module 1 sets the baseline: slowing down enough to notice, refining attention, and reconnecting “pleasure” with presence rather than escape.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/60">What people leave with</div><ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-white/75">
            <li>A practical attention ritual</li>
            <li>A new relationship with sensation</li>
            <li>Simple prompts they’ll reuse</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/60">Practice (starter)</div>
        <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-5 text-sm text-white/75">
          <li>Choose one sensory anchor (taste, breath, touch).</li>
          <li>Slow it down for 90 seconds.</li>
          <li>Name what you notice (no judging).</li>
          <li>Repeat daily for 7 days.</li>
        </ol>
